(Translated by Google) I was walking from the store, carrying groceries in Trabuco Canyon, when a motorcycle hit my right side, causing groceries to fly to the other side of the road. While it was happening, it caused another driver to lose control and hit three cars on the road. For my part, I fell and suffered neck injuries, but the other cars were damaged. The drivers of the damaged cars blamed me for causing the accident, and they all sued me wanting to be fined for the act. But it was the motorcycle rider who had crashed while driving in the pedestrian lane. I was shocked and scared by the lawsuits, so I called my friend who quickly gave me Mr. Kim's number. I called him, and he was quick on the scene and informed me how he was going to help me. As I write, I am free, and I believe in Daniel Kim for the fantastic work he did on this case.

(Original)
Estaba caminando desde la tienda, cargando víveres en Trabuco Canyon, cuando una motocicleta golpeó mi lado derecho, haciendo que los víveres volaran hasta el otro lado de la carretera. Mientras sucedía, causó que otro conductor perdiera el control y golpeó tres autos en la carretera. Por mi parte, me caí y experimenté lesiones en el cuello, pero los otros autos quedarón dañados. Los conductores de los autos dañados me culparon por causar el accidente, y todos me demandaron queriendo que me multasen por el acto. Pero fue el conductor de la motocicleta el que se había estrellado mientras conducía por el carril de peatones. Estaba en shock y asustado por las demandas, así que llamé a mi amigo que rápidamente me dio el número del Sr. Kim. Lo llamé, y él fue rápido a la escena y me informó sobre cómo me iba a ayudar. Mientras escribo, soy libre, y creo en Daniel Kim por el fantástico trabajo que hizo con este caso.< /text>

< Text>
Passing through Modesto I looked up the dog parks in the area and found this one to be the closest to me. We got there and the visual was not impressive. A large fenced in area with partial vegetation.shoehorned between a church and the four lane avenue. Littered with plastic chairs most of which should have been discarded last season. Upon entering the park I was warmly welcomed by two woman chatting near the gate. And every person I met there was equally as kind. None of the dogs, breeds running the gamut, we're ill tempered or mean-spirited. Quite a change from what one can expect at a dog park in Antioch. I left pleased my initial impressions were incorrect and refreshed by the kindness I felt.</Text>

This park is donated land from the adjoining church, it is completely fenced with a 3' fence which is nice. The lot itself is mostly sand, and there is one tree planted near the middle of the lot it is still a very small tree. The community donates lawn chairs and is responsible for bringing/providing water for the dogs and poop bags. I'm not sure who is responsible for emptying the trash but I am grateful that they do it. It's great to let your dog run off leash, but when it is hot outside it offers no shade.<//review>

<UserId.>115481397897684134617<//UserId.>< review>
We LOVE, LOVE, LOVE DogPile Dogs!

We used to bring our last dog to Wag Hotel, but with our new dog, we did some research and wanted to try something new.. And I'm SO glad we did because we absolutely LOVE the personal attention that Dogpile Dogs gives to all the great doggies there!

When you think about Wag Hotel, it's great, they have all these super fancy spa treatments for your dog (who could care less). What do dogs actually care about? They care about having a great time with other dogs. They care about personal connections with the humans watching them.

We always thought that overnight stays locked in a cold, hard, clear box were normal (at Wag Hotel), but after seeing the crate-free, cozy cots and mattresses at DogPile and multiple successful overnight stays, DogPile will forever be our go-to for our doggy day care and overnight stays. Not to mention, our dog never comes home smelling like pee anymore (a common occurrence at Wag).

Everyone at DogPile is personable, genuine, and loves dogs. It's family-run, the same folks are always there, so it's so much more personal than other doggy day cares. They truly take the time to play and get to know your dog.. Check out their Instagram page to see for yourself. The people are amazing, you get the same consistent care, and it's always fun to see posts of your dog on their Instagram page!</review>

The crew at dogpile were really patient with our pup, sent us updates and pics throughout her first day, and answered all my messages about her. Dogpile went above and beyond to take care of our little girl and we are so grateful. Our pup came home tired and happy! Cannot say enough good things about Dogpile. I have a rescue with terrible separation anxiety and he loves coming here.

Even though the facility is large and gives the dogs a ton of space to run around the service is so personal it feels like you are leaving your dog with family. Everyone who works here is so kind and really cares about all the dogs.

We prefer leaving our dog here vs having a sitter in our house as our dog is so well looked after. One trip our dog was getting anxious at night and the guys took him in to sleep with them. I have also gone in on cold days and they have put coats on all the short hair dogs. These are just 2 examples of the many tiny things they do to look after the dogs under their care. I could give you a dozen more.

Our dog always sprints in and then sleeps like a log when he gets home which otake as a good sign! THIS IS THE BEST DOGGIE DAY CARE IN SF!</review>

<username>Thanh H</username>< Review>
Share review

Embed review

Write an update

Edit review

9/30/2020
We've been taking our cavalier, Louis, to DogPile since February 2020 and he absolutely loves it! He generally has anxiety and is a stage 5 clinger, but when he realizes we are close to DogPile he starts tugging at his leash and is super excited to go inside. He doesn't even say goodbye to his mom!

DogPile has a huge outdoor/indoor space with lots of room for the pups to run around, Louis is exhausted when he comes home. We like that he's not stuck in a kennel or a small room the entire day. We were able to go inside before the pandemic and it was always clean, didn't smell, and the dogs looked happy and well-cared for. It's super easy to drop off Louis either for the day or if we have errands to run. Someone is always there and they are flexible with drop-off/pick-ups. The prices are reasonable and the DogPile team could not be nicer! They post pictures and videos on instagram (@dogpiledogs) and it's fun to see Louis and the other pups playing.< /Review>

We love Dogpile Dogs! Flat price from 7am to 7pm.

<gmap_id>0x808f7fbb1c2990cb:0x8f098dc18c4d769f<//gmap_id><UserId.>115586346351385364191< /UserId.><name>s roberts</name>< time>

<Resp>None< /Resp>< Review>
I have been bringing our dog here for about 6 months. She and I love it here. The staff is super friendly and responsive. There is off-street parking for easy drop-off and pick up. The facility is clean and spacious with a great drop-off entry area. The facility is separated by big and small dogs, and both have in-door and out-door play areas. The dogs are always calm at any time of day, and I have never heard a dog bark once while I am there! When I pick up my dog at the end of the day, classical music is playing, I can see my dog lounging on a dog cot, and she is exhausted from playing all day. We just left here for a week over the holidays, and when we picked her up she was definitely tired from a week of playing, but she was calm, and while I know she was probably happy to see me, she we was just super chilled-out. I cannot recommend Dogpile Dogs enough.< /Review>

Extremely good.  The ahi tuna appetizer was tremendous.  There is a sauce over the greens that would be great on the side as a dipping sauce.  The drinks were strong and good for the price.  The filets were melt in the mouth even at different temps.  The last bite was seriously as good as the first.  The dessert choices were limited, but I would have gotten the chocolate cake anyway.  It was just at the borderline of too strong of chocolate and perfectly right, a very narrow line.  Overall great location by the lake.  We sat indoors by the windows, but outdoors at sunset would be spectacular.  10/10.< /review>
</record>
</dataset><record>
<GmapID>0x809d6a247afc0843:0xe085269175ce1c7f< /GmapID>< Pictures>
None</Pictures>
<time>1601335838771<//time>< Review>
Maybe not an objective 5 star, but for the area I have a pretty good sense that this is the best restaurant in the north Lake Almanor area. We were visiting Lassen and staying in Chester in September 2020 and there was a serious dearth of restaurants worth eating at, let alone take food away from. Covid or no, the Italian place around the corner was the only other place that ranked. There was one other place that seemed to have a reasonable pub menu with good reviews in Chester, but when we got there we didn’t even enter because it looked like a non-stop super-spreader party. No masks and everyone was shoulder to shoulder. Hard pass.

But anyway, The Red Onion: great setting in lovely Westwood, friendly service, a cozy bar with a good drinks selection, and the rare ribeye steak I had there was fairly epic. My wife had the Salmon which was perfectly prepared as well on the skin making it oh-so flavorful. Get some veggies there because while the 4 stakes of asparagus that came with my meal were perfect, I kind felt guilty just eating a massive steal and potatoes.

I don’t write a lot of Google reviews but we were so grateful to find this place I just have to send them some props and so other people seeking vittles who crave a well-made dinner in a nice setting know here to go. It’s amazing how much you need a decent restaurant when one is hard to come by!

Only comment: the generic country music that constantly plays there (I was there twice) is pretty weak. I swear I heard ‘Werewolves of London’ come on but after the intro there were bland country lyrics that sounded exactly Warren Zevon’s classic song note for note, right down to the backup singers. Lies! Anyway, Red Onion, if you’re reading this... please mix the music up a little at least! I’m sure the wait staff would be grateful too. Otherwise I’ve got nothing but love for you!</Review>

< text>
I do not understand how this place has good reviews. I had the worst experience here. Top 3 worst Mexican restaurants I've ever been too. Table salsa mediocre at best and the bean dip is just very plain completely lacking any taste or flavor. I had the chicken enchilada with "red" mole sauce more like a brown sauce that was just awful. My mother and I also had a asada tacos and she also had a beef taco. We requested soft tacos and they came hard. When we asked the server she said they were the soft tacos they are just "not as fried as the hard tacos" which translated to them tasting soggy and stale. The beef taco had a strange mole sauce which was unexpected. If I could give this place zero stars I would.<//text>

111457969246074655269< /userid>
<username>Cynthia Ann Tanner< /username>< date>
1476579081626</date>
<Rate>4<//Rate>< text>
Great authentic Mexican Food with excellent service. Family owned and operated, the owners and staff are attentive and caring and all work hard to create a nice family atmosphere and to ensure everyone has a enjoyable and satisfying experience. Enjoy Dining-in or getting take-out, both are great ways to enjoy the great Mexican food La Villa has to offer. Prices are about average, the quantity of food is good, but the main reason for me is the food taste so good. Even though the chicken, beef, shrimp, carne asada and everything else is wonderful, if you're a pork fan like I am, you can't go wrong with the Pork Quesadilla Dinner and/or the Pork Soup, two of my very favorites.<//text>

< Review>

I went to AWS last week for the first time, and honestly, this place deserves 6 stars. This was the best auto shop experience I've ever had! First, Caleb, the owner and first person you meet when you walk in, is the kindest, most attentive, and most honest shop manager you could ever hope to run into. I ended up having to be there longer than expected due to some unforeseen issues with my car, and Caleb chatted me up, gave me a cup of coffee, and checked in with me several times to see how I was doing. During this time, I watched Caleb interact with several other customers and he was consistently patient, generous, and invested in the needs of his clients. He knows that, for many people, having a vehicle that runs well can mean the difference between functioning healthily and having your life fall apart.

The prices are reasonable and the work is thorough. I went in initially for an oil change and routine inspection service, and the technician found several issues, which I consented to being repaired on the spot. After completion, I was immediately emailed a very comprehensive inspection report with tons of details about the work and tests performed, and lots of before/after pictures. This was so helpful! Then, a few days later, I got an email from Caleb checking in to see how things were going. Everything was fine, he was just following up. This is beyond customer service, this is community service!

AWS Automotive is the only place I will take my car to get work done as long as I live here. It is evident that they view themselves as a part of the Ventura community and are incredibly responsible with how they run things as a result. It's places like this that make the entire town a better place!</Text>

<gmap_id>0x80e9ac5f6ccb22e9:0xc3b06be294cb0f38<//gmap_id><user_name>David DeHaan</user_name><Time>1550950212294</Time>< Review>
AWS Automotive is the best! Their great customer service, knowledge and commitment to their clients combined with their online inspection report complete with photos, a loaner car and attention to keeping the customer informed creates a great auto service experience that cannot be beat.
I am in Ventura for a few months and needed service on my Ford F350 diesel, a very special vehicle to me as it had belonged to my dad. I selected AWS Automotive because of their great reviews. Caleb and his technicians performed the requested service and a vehicle inspection where they found one brake completely worn out, metal-on-metal. Their Vehicle Inspection Report was available to me online and included photos of all the critical inspection points and pictures that detailed the brake issue. This report is a great consumer protection tool that gave me great confidence in their credibility and dedication. Lucky for me they found this problem early on so they were able to machine my existing brake surfaces instead of replacing my brake rotors which would have cost considerably more. They completed this additional work with installation OEM spec brake pads. The extra work was finished quickly and at a very fair price within the price quote they had provided. Additionally, they provided me with a loaner vehicle while this work was being done.
I am familiar with auto mechanical issues and I am always concerned when I cannot use my normal shop for service. I also worry that when a shop gets my vehicle on a hoist, they may find problem and quote an inflated price to fix it as they already have the vehicle in shop. AWS Automotive and Caleb earned my total trust and appreciation with their professional, high tech, customer oriented service. I will always return to AWS Automotive for work when I am in the area and highly recommend them to others. I only wish this was my home town so I could use them all the time for my auto service needs.</Review>

< Review>
When I first came to AWS, it was because my car's cooling system had a major problem.  I had already taken my car (an older Volvo sedan) to three other mechanics in the area (two of which were Volvo specialists), and even after two major repairs, no one could find a long-term solution to the problem.  My brother (a car freak) has been going to AWS for years and recommended I give them a try.  AWS thoroughly checked over my car, found the problems, and made the necessary repairs that ultimately fixed the issue with the cooling system.  I have kept AWS as my regular auto shop.  Every oil change, they have meticulously checked over the entire car, sent emailed photographs with descriptions depicting any located issues needing resolve, and have provided me with detailed explanations of maintenance needs along with various options depending on my financial restrictions at any given time.  It meant a lot that they would take the time to patiently answer any and all questions I had instead of hurrying me to make decisions or expecting me to simply take their recommendation at face value. <Time>1610678837633< /Time><rate>3<//rate><Review>The Sugarshack is one of those pit stops off I5 heading to or coming fro LA in San Clemente. This Covid-19 has really beaten and battered the restaurant industry here in California as I see the owner's eyes fail to hide his worries as he explains his menu.
Look, the meal was an bacon and cream cheese omelet and besides the $21 price tag it was decent. I probably pay half of that in Florida but thats besides the point. I will stop by again, hoping to see a glimmer of hope in the owners eyes when this pandemic starts to fade. I pray.</Review>< Pics>

< date>
1604106139094< /date>
< Review>
My family and I stop by Sugar Shack on our way home from our timeshare visit in San Diego each year. It has become a tradition going on seven years now.The staff is always friendly and the food is great. This visit I tried the chicken fried steak and eggs. So good! The chicken fried steak was a good size, the hash browns were crispy, the eggs cooked perfectly and the homemade biscuit and country gravy were delicious. Not many places serve good homemade biscuits. And if you haven't tried one of their cinnamon rolls (homemade from scratch every day) you are truly missing out. But get there early, they go fast!</Review>

< userid>
115259346877084290465</userid>
<username>Sara Mancilla</username>< date>
1468592722988< /date>
< Rate>
5</Rate>
< Review>
We stumbled upon this place totally out of the blue. We weren't sure about it at first, but we checked it out. Wow, are we glad we did!

Our server was extremely kind. She was understanding about three kids at a variety of ages, as well as my husband and me, and she catered to all of us, making sure we had everything we needed.

We were seated in the outside seating, which was a small patio outside of the main building where there are some tables set up. We were worried that we would be forgotten, but that was far from the truth. It felt we were in the main restaurant, but with a better view and fresh air.

The food was delicious, and the portions were huge! All the kids got one of the kids' plates, and they received almost as much food as we did for less than half the price, and they loved it. My husband got one of the omelets, and I got Eggs Benedict. I'm not a food critic nor expert, but, at least to me, they were both delicious.

The only bad thing I had to say about this place was the price of drinks, but everywhere is like that, so it's not even a complaint or a surprise.

If we're back in this area again, we know exactly where we're eating!<//Review>
